-- China Stocks: China Cosco, Cosco Shipping, Sany Heavy, SAIC
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-05-09T08:04:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/china-stocks-china-cosco-cosco-shipping-sany-heavy-saic.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in China trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
as of the close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index (SHCOMP) , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges,  slumped 40.3 points, or 1.7 percent,
to 2,408.59 at the close, the biggest drop since March 28. The
 CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)   declined 1.9 percent to 2,657.51.  China Cosco Holdings Co. (601919)  (601919 CH), the nation’s biggest
publicly traded shipping company, dropped 4.2 percent to 5.24
 yuan  and  Cosco Shipping Co. (600428)  (600428 CH) retreated 4.9 percent to
4.90 yuan.  Alexis Tsipras, leader of Greece’s Syriza party, said he
plans to form a government that would cancel bailout accords,
adding to uncertainty about Europe’s economic stability. That
could damp shipping demand, undermining efforts by lines to
raise rates.  Sany Heavy Industry Co. (600031)  (600031 CH), the biggest maker of
excavators, fell 3.4 percent to 14.31 yuan. Demand for
excavators dropped a “rather disappointing” 42 percent in
April, Nomura said, citing data from China Construction
Machinery Association.  SAIC Motor Corp. (600104)  (600104 CH), the largest Chinese
automaker,  slid 2.9 percent to 15.53 yuan.  Beiqi Foton Motor
Co. (600166)  (600166 CH), the biggest commercial-vehicle maker, lost 3.3
percent to 8.57 yuan  slid 2.9 percent. The Xinhua News Agency
said China will ban executives at state-owned companies from
excessive spending on items such as cars.  To contact the reporter on this story:
